         <abstract>
            <p>A procedure for the numerical approximation of the Cauchy problem for the following linear parabolic partial differential equation is defined: $$u_t - (p(x)u_x)_x + q(x)u = 0,\quad 0 &lt; x &lt; 1, 0 &lt; t \leqslant T;\quad u(0, t) = f_1(t),\\ 0 &lt; t \leqslant T;\quad u(1, t) = f_2(t),\quad 0 &lt; t \leqslant T; \quad p(0)u_x(0, t) = g(t),\\0 &lt; t_0 \leqslant t \leqslant T;\quad |u(x, t)| \leqslant M, \quad 0 \leqslant x \leqslant 1, 0 \leqslant t \leqslant T$$. The procedure involves Galerkin-type numerical methods for related parabolic initial boundary-value problems and a linear programming problem. Explicit a priori error estimates are presented for the entire discrete procedure when the data $f_1, f_2$, and $g$ are known only approximately.</p>
          </abstract>
